    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1548"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1548">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/617.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 8, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: With further reference to the
                    subject of the confiscation of the water works of Mazatlan I beg to quote the
                    text of a telegram which I have received to-day: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Ayuntamiento executed seizure water supply decree June 6, in spite order
                            from Governor to suspend and protest of British American and Spanish
                            representatives. Manager refused to give possession. However, they are
                            occupying office and taking inventory, without intervention of company’s
                            representatives. As the possessions of the company in the hands of those
                            people, though for a short time, will be the ruin and destruction of the
                            company, I beg your excellency for your valuable effort in order to
                            avoid this offense as soon as possible.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
